FROM student st, test_roster tr, STG_PARAM_WINSCR_TB stg, STG_TEST_ROSTER str

st.student_id = tr.student_id AND tr.customer_id = stg.customer_id AND str.test_roster_id = tr.test_roster_id AND str.student_id = tr.student_id

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This source qualifier transformation is having sql override query used to get the needed fields from TEST_ROSTER, TEST_ADMIN, TEST_CATALOG and STG_PARAM_WINSCR_TB
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_TEST_ADMIN

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
SELECT TEST_ROSTER.customer_id, TEST_ADMIN.product_id, TEST_ROSTER.student_id, TEST_CATALOG.test_catalog_id, TEST_CATALOG.item_set_id, COUNT (TEST_ADMIN.test_admin_id)
FROM TEST_ROSTER, TEST_ADMIN, TEST_CATALOG, stg_param_winscr_tb
WHERE TEST_ROSTER.test_admin_id = TEST_ADMIN.test_admin_id
AND TEST_ADMIN.test_catalog_id = TEST_CATALOG.test_catalog_id AND TEST_ROSTER.customer_id = TEST_ADMIN.customer_id AND TEST_ADMIN.product_id = TEST_CATALOG.product_id AND TEST_ROSTER.customer_id = stg_param_winscr_tb.customer_id AND TEST_ADMIN.product_id = stg_param_winscr_tb.product_id AND TEST_ROSTER.activation_status = 'AC' AND TEST_ROSTER.test_completion_status NOT IN ('NT', 'SC')
AND ( EXISTS (SELECT NULL FROM ITEM_RESPONSE ir WHERE ir.test_roster_id = TEST_ROSTER.test_roster_id) OR EXISTS (SELECT NULL FROM ITEM_RESPONSE_CR irc WHERE irc.test_roster_id = TEST_ROSTER.test_roster_id) )
GROUP BY TEST_ROSTER.customer_id, TEST_ROSTER.student_id, TEST_ADMIN.product_id, TEST_CATALOG.test_catalog_id, TEST_CATALOG.item_set_id
HAVING COUNT (TEST_ADMIN.test_admin_id) > 1

TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_Eiss_Validity_Check

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This task is to start the EISS Workflow.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: Start

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_ST_Extract mapping, which in turn,creates the 'ST'(Student Test) records in the STG_EISS_TB . Also all ST data are formatted and concatenated into a single field so as to facilitate creating the ST records in the Winscore file.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_ST_Extract

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_Winscore mapping. The mapping uses a stored procedure to load the EISS data from STG_EISS_TB into STG_EISS_LOAD_TB in proper hierarchical form as needed in the EISS file. Then the mapping loads all the EISS data from the staging table into a flat file (eiss.dat). A shell script is then utilized to split the file generated by the process into multiple files based on district with proper file name format.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_Winscore

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_OU_Extract mapping, which in turn,creates the 'OU'(OpUnit/District Records) records in the STG_EISS_TB . Also all OU data are formatted and concatenated into a single field so as to facilitate creating the GH records in the Winscore file.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_OU_Extract

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_SH_Extract mapping, which in turn,creates the 'SH'(School Records) records in the STG_EISS_TB . Also all SH data are formatted and concatenated into a single field so as to facilitate creating the SH records in the Winscore file.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_SH_Extract

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session executes the mapping m_O_Stud_Admin_Id_Check which in turn check the existence of more than one TEST_ADMIN_ID for particular STUDENT_ID for TEST_CATALOG_ID. IF there is more than one TEST_ADMIN_ID session will be ABORTED.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_Eiss_m_O_Stud_Admin_Id_Check

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_SR_Extract mapping, which in turn,creates the 'SR'(Student Records) records in the STG_EISS_TB . Also all SR data are formatted and concatenated into a single field so as to facilitate creating the SR records in the Winscore file.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_SR_Extract

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session is used to execute the m_O_GH_Extract mapping, which in turn,creates the 'GH'(Group/Class Records) records in the STG_EISS_TB . Also all GH data are formatted and concatenated into a single field so as to facilitate creating the GH records in the Winscore file.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_O_GH_Extract
